                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <date>May 1880</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>My dear Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I send you herewith but<lb/> a few pages of the Cozri as I see from\n                yr<lb/> last number that you have desired<add>?</add> several<lb/> articles for the\n                next number. Why do you persist<lb/> in calling me “<persName>Adolph</persName>”?\n                This not my name and<lb/> strange to say, I find that most of the letters\n                coming<lb/> from the country <del>have adopted the</del> are addressed<lb/> to\n                    <persName>Dr. Adolph</persName> etc. So pray do not affix any<lb/> longer that\n                name.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Why did you not mention in yr last<lb/> number the lectures\n                delivered by myself &amp; <persName>Dr Raphall</persName><lb/> before<add>?</add>\n                the Geographic Society, as you must have<lb/> seen a report in every <placeName>New\n                    York</placeName> Paper. It is<lb/> now too late to speak of it, but it was<lb/>\n                a very successful effort on my part.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have written a series of articles<lb/> on “the Greeks, Romans, and\n                Judeans” with the</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wg93/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
